reviews.review: Not a perfect or flawless movie. But it gets five stars for being that absolute best it could have been. It also does so much more character development than the last two combined. Makes it feel as if each character had a consistent arc.
Fun movie. Too much happening at once though

The biggest disappointment of this year. A lot of bad writing, a lot of bad director decisions. I was a huge fan of the new trilogy, but after that abomination? Guess, everyone we're right. Ryan Johnson, miss you like crazy, you were amazing! Adam Driver, you're the best actor out there and I'm glad we're all living in the same period of time! JJ, you're rat.

The Rise of Skywalker was a movie with a lot to say and little time to do it in. The pace was frenetic with high and low moments. 

How do you satisfy fans by both honoring the past and present characters in one movie? In short, you can't. However, the Rise of Skywalker gives it an admirable try and will leave you entertained. 

The final trilogy is a solid addition to the Star Wars universe, but Disney would be wise to follow the Kevin Feige Marvel model loosely planning out a storyline that connects while letting different directors create their own Star Wars movie.
The Rise of Skywalker though a visual delight fails to deliver a epic conclusion of the trilogy with a rushed pacing and unusual plot choices.
The people hating on this are just jumping on a bandwagon with no real reason to hate on it. This movie was amazing! Not perfect but still amazing.
Damage repaired !!! A must see movie. The Skywalker saga is completed.

Okay. Here it is. My review of Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker. It is not a must see. I wish it was otherwise, but there it is. It does tie up all the loose ends, but one. There are cameos all over the place and the dialog, at times, is hookie. A few feel good moments that you cheer for and a couple that you might cry over.
If you must see it in theaters because, like me you have seen them all in a theater at one time or another, there is No NEED to see it on opening weekend.
Hope this helps you plan your movie going plans.
It wasnt anything special. A typical JJ Abrams popcorn movie.
